{{L.}} ''[[Maria]]'', from {{Gr.}} ''[[Μαρία]]'' ([[Maria]]), ''[[Μαριάμ]]'' (Mariam), from Aramaic ''[[מרים]]'' (Maryām), bitter, from a root '''מר''' (<small>MR</small>) meaning "to be bitter"; the name corresponds to the Hebrew ''[[מרים]]'' (Miryām), '''[[Miriam]]'''

